dcterms:description: The Join Order Benchmark (JOB) consists of queries with 3 to 16 joins, with an average of 8 joins per query. It includes 33 different query structures, each existing in 2 to 6 different variants, resulting in a query set of 113 queries. The queries are realistic and designed to answer questions of a movie enthusiast.
dcterms:title: Join Order Benchmark (JOB)

dcterms:description: The IMDB dataset is a real-world dataset consisting of 21 tables containing information about movies and movie-related facts like actors and directors. It is based on data that is highly correlated and non-uniformly distributed.
dcterms:title: IMDB dataset
